ty of the Free Trade Area of the Asia-Pacific (FTAAP) proposal and looks at alternative modalities for achieving free trade and investment in the Asia-Pacific. The report includes trade policy perspectives from the three largest economies of the region: the United States, China and Japan, lessons from similar proposals such as the Free Trade Area of the Americas (FTAA), possible convergence among the many preferential trade agreements (PTAs) in the region, and alternative approaches to regional economic integration.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aFree tradezAsia. 0aFree tradezPacific Area. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / International Relations / Treaties.2bisacsh1 aAggarwal, Vinod K., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBergsten, C. Fred, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBin, Sheng, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrison, Charles E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMorrison, Charles E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPedrosa, Eduardo, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aScollay, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSoesastro, Hadi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStephenson, Sherry M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aUrata, Shujiro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aYue, Chia Siow, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAsian Studies Backlist (2000-2014) eBook Packagez978311064977208iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertISEAS Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2015z978311066300608iTitle is part of eBook